New Records: Australia secured an eighth men's 50-over World Cup final for Australia
Key Match Events: Pat Cummins made a sparkling catch and took 2 wickets
Tabraiz Shamsi took 2 wickets for South Africa
Post-Match Reflections: Rob Walter, South Africa's head coach, said that losing a game you're in a position to win is not a choke, but rather being behind the eight-ball from the start
Pat Cummins noted the turn and called on Travis Head's part-time tweakers for the 31st over, which proved a masterstroke
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on a capricious, used pitch
The crowd was 48,000 locals, plus a sprinkling of travelling fans
South Africa had simply been unable to wriggle free from a canary yellow cage at the outset
The match was a Test-match battle out in the middle
